<br>
The quests start in the Gulf of Gunthak at an NPC named Vira. She's a gnome and she is located in a small building on the opposite side of the lighthouse from the dock. <br>
<br>
Hail Vira and follow her prompts. She'll ask you to bring her two items: Flicker of Lava and Flicker of the Sea. Both of these items are dropped of Luggdals in the Gulf of Gunthak. If you go due south from the lighthouse you'll come to a beach and just beyond that is a network of tunnels where you can get to at least two different &quot;towns&quot;.<br>
<br>
One town has Luggdals out in the open, whereas they are located in the center of a fort in the other town. I fought at the fort just because it was the first one I came across. There are lots of small buildings surrounding the fort with pirates in them. As a Dark Elf, they were kos to me. I don't know about any other races.<br>
<br>
Anyway, there's a lot of them and some are close together. They were all green and light blue to me at lvl 56 and were pretty easy to handle. They could be a problem though for lower levels, and even higher levels if you get a bunch of them on you.<br>
<br>
It took about 2 hours of clearing the inside of the fort for me to get the items. Turn those back in to Vira and she will give you a Vial of Liquid. She'll instruct you to take it to her sister, named Vera, in the Temple of Sol Ro (remember her from your focus item quests?). Give the vial to Vera and she will give you a note to take back to Vira in the Gulf of Gunthak. <br>
<br>
When you give the note to Vira, you will be rewarded with the spell Primal Remedy. Vira will then ask for your assistance with another matter. Basically, she wants three &quot;elements&quot; from Luggdals in the Turigan (sp?) mines. <br>
<br>
That's where I stopped and logged for the night. I plan on working on this one again tomorrow and I will post any info then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmatelemental>XalmatElemental</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#333333>(2/25/03 7:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1854.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LoY Spell Quests</span><hr size=1> Isn't Vira the name of that gnome in Temple of Solusek Ro that gives out the focus items? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolf5>wolf5</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(2/25/03 8:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1854.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LoY Spell Quests</span><hr size=1> He prob just mixed the names up when writing. Still... good job. I guess there will be many mages running around tonite to get that 1st spell.<br>
